331
00:29:00.850 --> 00:29:02.442
Where's Mom and Dad?

332
00:29:02.552 --> 00:29:03.814
They'll be down in a minute.

333
00:29:03.920 --> 00:29:07.481
Patrick's vent alarm is going off,
so they need to fix it.


334
00:29:07.590 --> 00:29:10.388
His alarm goes off even more than mine.

335
00:29:18.601 --> 00:29:21.934
So, what's your deal? You married?

336
00:29:23.172 --> 00:29:24.833
Do you have a wife?

337
00:29:25.341 --> 00:29:27.172
Ex-wives. Two of 'em.

338
00:29:27.276 --> 00:29:30.905
- Yeah? How come?
- 'Cause I'm so easy to get along with.


339
00:29:31.781 --> 00:29:35.182
- Any other questions?
- No. Your turn to ask one.


340
00:29:37.687 --> 00:29:39.177
You're probably wondering
what grade I'm in.


341
00:29:39.288 --> 00:29:41.756
- What grade are you in?
- I'm in third.


342
00:29:41.891 --> 00:29:45.588
My hobbies are video games and penguins.
How about you?


343
00:29:46.362 --> 00:29:49.854
- I already graduated.
- No, I mean hobbies.


344
00:29:52.635 --> 00:29:53.761
Mostly I just work.

345
00:29:53.870 --> 00:29:57.169
Little bass fishing
every once in a while, but...


346
00:29:59.542 --> 00:30:00.941
What's your favorite subject?

347
00:30:01.043 --> 00:30:05.377
I'm good at reading, but I like P.E. Best,
especially the sprint races.


348
00:30:05.481 --> 00:30:06.709
Sprint races?

349
00:30:06.816 --> 00:30:09.011
- Wanna see?
- Sure.


350
00:30:14.490 --> 00:30:15.889
Come on.

351
00:30:18.561 --> 00:30:20.859
- Is he here yet?
- I don't know.


352
00:30:29.839 --> 00:30:31.773
I'm gonna win!

353
00:30:32.475 --> 00:30:34.375
Come on, slowpoke.

354
00:30:38.748 --> 00:30:40.443
Yeah, I won!

355
00:30:41.350 --> 00:30:42.715
I won.

356
00:30:43.152 --> 00:30:44.551
Oh, yeah.

357
00:30:45.187 --> 00:30:47.417
Told you I'm gonna beat you.

358
00:30:48.457 --> 00:30:49.719
Hi.

359
00:30:50.993 --> 00:30:53.587
Dr. Stonehill has two ex-wives.

360
00:30:53.696 --> 00:30:55.994
- I see that Megan's introduced herself.
- Yeah.


361
00:30:56.098 --> 00:30:58.089
- How are you, Dr. Stonehill?
- I'm okay, thank you.


362
00:30:58.200 --> 00:31:00.134
- This is Aileen, my wife.
- So nice to meet you.


363
00:31:00.269 --> 00:31:02.396
- And John Jr.
- Hello.


364
00:31:02.505 --> 00:31:03.767
- Here's Patrick.
- Hi.


365
00:31:03.873 --> 00:31:06.637
- Hey, Patrick.
- I think we should probably go inside.


366
00:31:06.909 --> 00:31:08.069
Yeah, come on inside.

367
00:31:08.177 --> 00:31:11.078
Megan, we'll see you inside. Come on.

368
00:31:16.552 --> 00:31:18.816
- Night, Patrick.
- Good night.


369
00:31:19.455 --> 00:31:20.683
Night, SpongeBob.

370
00:31:20.790 --> 00:31:24.157
- You gotta say good night to Dr. Stonehill.
- Kiss SpongeBob.


371
00:31:31.033 --> 00:31:32.967
- Good night.
- Good night, son.


372
00:31:34.570 --> 00:31:36.265
Good night, Patrick.

373
00:31:36.372 --> 00:31:39.535
I'm not gonna say it again. 
It is bedtime now.

374
00:31:40.009 --> 00:31:41.670
It's for him.

375
00:31:44.013 --> 00:31:47.847
- Me?
- For good luck. For bass fishing.


376
00:31:48.884 --> 00:31:50.112
Thank you.

377
00:31:52.655 --> 00:31:54.384
You like it?

378
00:31:54.523 --> 00:31:58.983
Well, sure. A happy-go-lucky little fellow,
lots of personality, huh?


379
00:31:59.929 --> 00:32:02.864
- He's a plastic toy.
- I know.


380
00:32:03.332 --> 00:32:04.799
Here's the father-daughter dance.

381
00:32:04.900 --> 00:32:08.301
You haven't lived until you've seen
Megan do the Wheelchair Watusi.


382
00:32:08.404 --> 00:32:09.894
Here you go.

383
00:32:10.006 --> 00:32:13.908
- Go ahead and eat the cobbler while it's hot.
- Smells great, honey.


384
00:32:15.111 --> 00:32:16.578
This was hilarious.

385
00:32:16.679 --> 00:32:20.342
Bob, we went to this dude ranch.
All right if I call you Bob?


386
00:32:20.449 --> 00:32:25.386
You got a check for a half-million dollars,
hell, you can call me Peggy Sue.


387
00:32:28.357 --> 00:32:29.881
I'll just...

388
00:32:40.503 --> 00:32:42.027
Well, Bob.

389
00:32:42.672 --> 00:32:47.302
This is the first installment
against the promised half a million.


390
00:32:58.721 --> 00:33:01.417
Tell you the truth,
that's more than I expected.


391
00:33:01.524 --> 00:33:04.618
Dr. Stonehill, we promise that...

392
00:33:04.727 --> 00:33:06.524
- Yeah, I know.
- Lf... In enough time, then...


393
00:33:06.629 --> 00:33:08.597
I know. I know.

394
00:33:10.199 --> 00:33:13.532
You can learn a lot about a person
on the Internet these days.


395
00:33:13.636 --> 00:33:17.128
Learn about a working-class kid
from New Jersey,


396
00:33:17.239 --> 00:33:20.208
worked his way through
Harvard Business School,


397
00:33:20.309 --> 00:33:22.777
clawing his way up the ladder
at Bristol-Myers.


398
00:33:22.912 --> 00:33:24.379
But what Google can't tell you

399
00:33:24.480 --> 00:33:26.948
is that this scared, desperate, bullshitting
son of a bitch...


400
00:33:27.049 --> 00:33:28.812
- Wait just a minute...
- Don't interrupt.


401
00:33:28.918 --> 00:33:32.251
Will do and say whatever it takes
to get results.


402
00:33:33.422 --> 00:33:36.858
Which is why you and me are going
into business together, Jersey.


403
00:33:36.959 --> 00:33:38.119
Excuse me?

404
00:33:38.227 --> 00:33:40.491
I'm tired of begging breadcrumbs
from the university


405
00:33:40.596 --> 00:33:43.156
and giving them the patents to my ideas.

406
00:33:43.265 --> 00:33:46.063
They don't value my work. You do,

407
00:33:46.836 --> 00:33:49.498
which is why I'm
setting up my own shop.

408
00:33:49.605 --> 00:33:50.970
Figure any dude in a business suit

409
00:33:51.073 --> 00:33:53.200
can help me raise venture capital
and run the company,


410
00:33:53.309 --> 00:33:57.871
but who's gonna be half as motivated as
a dad who's trying to save his own kids?


411
00:33:57.980 --> 00:33:59.811
So, this is...

412
00:33:59.915 --> 00:34:02.383
So this is the shittiest offer
you're ever gonna get.


413
00:34:02.485 --> 00:34:06.478
