lousy working conditions,


414
00:34:06.589 --> 00:34:10.548
plus, if we raise the money,
you're gonna have to relocate to Nebraska.


415
00:34:15.197 --> 00:34:16.721
And with the right business plan,

416
00:34:16.832 --> 00:34:20.768
I can also promise you
a working enzyme for Pompe disease.


417
00:34:21.537 --> 00:34:25.405
I can't cure your kids, you know that.
They're always gonna be in wheelchairs,


418
00:34:26.776 --> 00:34:29.438
but I think I can save their lives.

419
00:34:34.416 --> 00:34:36.281
Outstanding cobbler.

420
00:34:39.021 --> 00:34:43.685
Okay, okay.
So, we agree we can't uproot the kids.


421
00:34:44.527 --> 00:34:46.654
What if Stonehill fails?

422
00:34:50.199 --> 00:34:54.101
Or what if he succeeds too late
to help Megs and Patrick?


423
00:34:54.203 --> 00:34:56.535
- Then what?
- I know.


424
00:34:57.673 --> 00:35:02.337
If we're gonna lose them young, you want
to spend every minute you can with them.


425
00:35:09.552 --> 00:35:13.249
John, that day that you flew to Nebraska,

426
00:35:13.355 --> 00:35:16.882
when you suddenly just ditched work and...

427
00:35:19.361 --> 00:35:22.853
My God, I thought you'd lost it.
You scared me.


428
00:35:23.599 --> 00:35:26.159
But once we rolled our sleeves up,

429
00:35:26.268 --> 00:35:30.500
and we started fundraising
and meeting other Pompe families,


430
00:35:33.409 --> 00:35:35.377
it made me feel like...

431
00:35:35.811 --> 00:35:38.041
I mean, do we just accept our fate

432
00:35:38.147 --> 00:35:41.742
and do what we're told
by all the well-meaning doctors


433
00:35:43.052 --> 00:35:46.886
and wait for the worst to happen,
or do we fight it?


434
00:35:49.625 --> 00:35:53.391
<i>I think you're making a mistake. 
I really do.</i>

435
00:35:53.996 --> 00:35:58.092
Even if you were credible as a CEO,
which you are not,


436
00:35:59.468 --> 00:36:04.371
the odds against you are crushing.
Nine out of 10 biotechs crash and burn.


437
00:36:04.473 --> 00:36:08.705
So where does that leave your kids
when their dad is flat broke


438
00:36:09.345 --> 00:36:12.872
with no job and no health insurance?

439
00:36:13.182 --> 00:36:14.240
Now, if you stay at Bristol,

440
00:36:14.350 --> 00:36:18.582
the guys upstairs are ready to put you in
the VP slot at the end of the third quarter


441
00:36:18.687 --> 00:36:20.882
with a 40% salary bump.

442
00:36:21.690 --> 00:36:22.884
John.

443
00:36:24.760 --> 00:36:27.524
Your family's gonna need that money,
aren't they?


444
00:36:27.630 --> 00:36:30.360
Pete, you're right. 
This is crazy.

445
00:36:31.734 --> 00:36:33.634
I'm chasing the wind.

446
00:36:34.904 --> 00:36:36.872
But I can't just

447
00:36:38.908 --> 00:36:42.071
sit around and wait
for my kids to die.

448
00:36:43.946 --> 00:36:45.538
I can't do it.

449
00:37:08.103 --> 00:37:11.072
<i>You have arrived at your destination.</i>

450
00:37:25.955 --> 00:37:28.150
Come on in. It's open.

451
00:37:28.791 --> 00:37:30.452
- Hey, there, Bob.
- Hey, John.


452
00:37:30.559 --> 00:37:31.583
How are you?

453
00:37:31.694 --> 00:37:33.958
- You have trouble finding me?
- No problem.


454
00:37:34.063 --> 00:37:35.826
- Sit down.
- Thanks.


455
00:37:42.638 --> 00:37:45.539
Ex-wife. She loved cats.

456
00:37:49.345 --> 00:37:52.007
Well, say, what do we...

457
00:37:53.916 --> 00:37:57.613
What are we gonna do?
How about we work up a strategy


458
00:37:57.720 --> 00:38:00.518
for the meeting at Renzler next week?

459
00:38:03.225 --> 00:38:05.659
We don't need to show those guys anything.

460
00:38:06.095 --> 00:38:07.494
The meeting's a formality.

