00:56:24.058 --> 00:56:29.462
I want you to go toe-to-toe
with Zymagen's scientists.


704
00:56:29.564 --> 00:56:33.295
- Prove to them that your enzyme is best.
- I can do that.


705
00:56:33.434 --> 00:56:35.664
That's the reason I've entered
into conversations with them


706
00:56:35.770 --> 00:56:38.068
to buy our company.

707
00:56:38.172 --> 00:56:40.504
You're telling me? 
You're not asking me?

708
00:56:40.608 --> 00:56:44.977
Come on, Bob.
I am just being fiscally responsible.


709
00:56:45.079 --> 00:56:48.742
Nobody is gonna tell me
how to run my lab!

710
00:56:48.850 --> 00:56:52.377
If I can engineer a deal,
and that is a really big "if,"


711
00:56:52.487 --> 00:56:55.012
you're going to have to forgive me
for all the money I'm gonna make you.


712
00:56:55.123 --> 00:56:57.057
I don't care about money.

713
00:56:57.158 --> 00:57:01.117
I'm a scientist.
I care about more important things than that.


714
00:57:01.629 --> 00:57:05.565
Don't you tell me about
more important things to care about.


715
00:57:06.834 --> 00:57:08.426
Do the math.

716
00:57:09.437 --> 00:57:14.739
Either we sell the company
and get a huge cash infusion,


717
00:57:16.511 --> 00:57:19.071
or the investors will shut us down.

718
00:57:29.056 --> 00:57:30.785
Where you going?

719
00:57:34.896 --> 00:57:39.333
I'm gonna go take a crap,
if that meets with your fiscal approval.


720
00:57:58.553 --> 00:58:01.750
What, they can't drive from the airport
like ordinary people?


721
00:58:01.856 --> 00:58:04.324
Bob, we need to make this happen.

722
00:58:06.327 --> 00:58:08.454
They're gonna ask us some tough questions.

723
00:58:08.896 --> 00:58:13.060
Don't take 'em personally, all right?
All right?


724
00:58:24.779 --> 00:58:28.237
These lab results confirm
what I've been preaching for years,


725
00:58:28.416 --> 00:58:32.182
that phosphorylation is key
to enzyme absorption.


726
00:58:33.054 --> 00:58:35.522
My theory works for Pompe,

727
00:58:35.623 --> 00:58:39.491
and eventually it'll work for
enzyme replacement therapies


728
00:58:39.594 --> 00:58:42.358
for other lysosomal storage disorders.

729
00:58:42.964 --> 00:58:46.092
- Is it too complicated?
- Too complicated?


730
00:58:46.200 --> 00:58:50.227
The number of variables built into
your approach are mind-boggling.


731
00:58:50.338 --> 00:58:53.671
I mean, Jesus, if you get even
one piece wrong in the synthesis,


732
00:58:53.774 --> 00:58:56.834
just one carbohydrate ends up
in the wrong position...


733
00:58:56.944 --> 00:59:00.243
Well, it's gotta be done right,
like anything worth doing.


734
00:59:00.781 --> 00:59:03.545
You've never actually gotten
a drug approved.


735
00:59:03.651 --> 00:59:08.554
Isn't it naive to think you can solve
these kinds of manufacturing challenges?


736
00:59:14.395 --> 00:59:16.522
Bob? Bob?

737
00:59:17.832 --> 00:59:20.528
You're right, I'm a theory guy.

738
00:59:21.502 --> 00:59:23.697
My head is in the clouds.

739
00:59:25.640 --> 00:59:27.767
Which is why we need you.

740
00:59:30.344 --> 00:59:32.642
Unless, of course, your reputation

741
00:59:32.780 --> 00:59:36.614
for solving protein-manufacturing problems
is undeserved.


742
00:59:38.786 --> 00:59:40.151
Nice one.

743
00:59:41.255 --> 00:59:46.090
- I still need to hear about profitability.
- Certainly, certainly.


744
00:59:46.627 --> 00:59:51.997
As you know, this is not
a one-time treatment. It's a lifelong therapy.


745
00:59:52.099 --> 00:59:53.896
And these patients,

746
00:59:54.001 --> 00:59:59.940
they are going to generate revenue
over the span of their lifetime that is...


747
01:00:00.041 --> 01:00:04.171
But even if you make a usable enzyme,
clearly it won't work for all patients.


748
01:00:04.278 --> 01:00:07.770
So, what survival rate do we need
to achieve a robust profit?


749
01:00:07.882 --> 01:00:11.841
What rate of patient death
can be defined as acceptable loss?


750
01:00:12.787 --> 01:00:14.778
Acceptable loss?

751
01:00:20.528 --> 01:00:22.655
I understand the question.

752
01:00:25.366 --> 01:00:31.305
Because the profit margins on this
orphan drug are so incredibly high, the...


753
01:00:32.673 --> 01:00:38.407
Even with a mortality rate of,
say, 25% over five years still indicates


754
01:00:38.512 --> 01:00:44.473
that there is a highly lucrative
revenue source to be realized.


755
01:00:59.567 --> 01:01:01.797
Gentlemen, we have a deal.

756
01:01:49.417 --> 01:01:52.215
Dr. Robert Stonehill to see Barry Renee.

757
01:01:55.623 --> 01:01:58.922
I have a Dr. Robert Stonehill
to see Dr. Renee.


758
01:02:01.061 --> 01:02:04.053
- Sir, you need to be cleared.
- I'm just gonna use the restroom.


759
01:02:04.165 --> 01:02:07.066
- You need to be cleared to do that, sir.
- Just need to...


760
01:02:07.168 --> 01:02:10.399
- You need a security badge.
- Jesus.


761
01:02:14.141 --> 01:02:17.702
Well, can I have a security badge
so I can go take a pee?


762
01:02:17.912 --> 01:02:19.607
Yes, sir. He will give that to you.

763
01:02:27.988 --> 01:02:30.548
- Hey, Bob.
- Hey, John.


764
01:02:30.658 --> 01:02:32.785
You getting comfortable?

765
01:02:33.661 --> 01:02:35.595
Define "comfortable."

766
01:02:40.000 --> 01:02:42.161
You haven't cashed it yet?

767
01:02:43.137 --> 01:02:45.128
I haven't earned it yet.

768
01:02:46.173 --> 01:02:49.165
I'll cash it when
we have a usable enzyme.

769
01:03:07.628 --> 01:03:10.222
Well, it sure is beautiful.

770
01:03:16.237 --> 01:03:18.000
It sure is big.

771
01:03:19.073 --> 01:03:20.870
The kids love it.

772
01:03:28.148 --> 01:03:29.809
Seize the day.

773
01:03:34.288 --> 01:03:35.585
Okay.

774
01:03:46.300 --> 01:03:47.790
I'm stuck on this call.

775
01:03:47.902 --> 01:03:51.065
Just wanted to let you know how thrilled
we are to have you onboard, John.


776
01:03:51.171 --> 01:03:52.798
It's an honor.

777
01:03:53.507 --> 01:03:55.634
- You remember Dr. Kent Webber.
- Of course.


778
01:03:55.743 --> 01:03:57.142
- It's good to see you again.
- Good to see you, too.


779
01:03:57.244 --> 01:04:00.111
I'll let the two
of you get into it.

780
01:04:00.214 --> 01:04:03.377
- I'm expecting great things.
- Yes, sir.


781
01:04:07.321 --> 01:04:12.156
I've got some pretty good ideas
about how to help the flow of information


782
01:04:12.259 --> 01:04:14.250
between the four core enzyme groups.

783
01:04:14.361 --> 01:04:17.762
Whoa, John, slow down.
That's not our established procedure.


784
01:04:17.865 --> 01:04:18.957
Pardon me?

785
01:04:19.066 --> 01:04:22.900
The four core teams are essentially
in competition with each other.


786
01:04:23.003 --> 01:04:25.995
It's an entrepreneurial model. It works.

787
01:04:26.106 --> 01:04:30.805
I'm all for competition,
but surely there must be some channel


788
01:04:30.911 --> 01:04:37.578
for allowing sharing scientific insights
that can help develop all four enzymes.


789
01:04:37.952 --> 01:04:42.685
John, in the interest of saving us time,
let me be blunt.


790
01:04:43.958 --> 01:04:46.153
Most of the scientists
here don't like the idea

791
01:04:46.260 --> 01:04:50.356
of having a non-scientist
as senior VP of the Pompe program.


792
01:04:51.899 --> 01:04:53.924
Especially one whose objectivity

793
01:04:54.034 --> 01:04:57.765
might be clouded
by having children with the disease.


794
01:04:58.906 --> 01:05:02.103
I'm telling you this
in your own best interests.


795
01:05:02.643 --> 01:05:05.009
Erich wanted to buy Stonehill's ideas,

796
01:05:05.112 --> 01:05:09.742
and he couldn't do that without also
swallowing you as part of the pill.


797
01:05:12.486 --> 01:05:16.582
My advice to you, John,
is to keep your head down.


798
01:05:19.560 --> 01:05:23.052
- Thank you for that wisdom.
- You're very welcome.


799
01:05:27.267 --> 01:05:28.235
All of your lab notebooks must be submitted
to the review committee!


800
01:05:28.235 --> 01:05:30.203
All of your lab notebooks must be submitted
to the review committee!


801
01:05:30.304 --> 01:05:32.795
This is my lab now! Get out!

802
01:05:32.906 --> 01:05:35.136
I'm just trying to explain the protocol!

803
01:05:35.242 --> 01:05:38.211
- You're wasting my time.
- Dr. Stonehill...


804
01:05:38.746 --> 01:05:39.974
Fine.

805
01:05:45.953 --> 01:05:47.250
What do you want?

806
01:05:47.955 --> 01:05:52.983
I just dropped by to say that I think
that we might be missing an opportunity


807
01:05:53.127 --> 01:05:55.960
to open a dialogue
with the other three core teams.


808
01:05:56.096 --> 01:05:59.657
The other core teams? Core teams.

809
01:05:59.800 --> 01:06:01.290
Core bullshit.

810
01:06:02.269 --> 01:06:04.499
I'll come back another time.

811
01:06:08.208 --> 01:06:11.336
The decline in muscle strength
is very troubling, of course,


812
01:06:11.445 --> 01:06:14.778
but it's really, in both kids,

813
01:06:14.882 --> 01:06:19.444
the organ enlargement, the liver,
and especially the heart,


814
01:06:19.553 --> 01:06:22.351
that's the real threat to their lives.

815
01:06:23.190 --> 01:06:26.387
